{{Infobox glacier | name = Balletto Glacier | photo = Kilimanjaro Glaciers.jpg | photo_caption = NASA image from 2004 with locations of major glaciers on Mount Kilimanjaro. Balletto Glacier is marked at bottom left near Diamond Glacier. Click on image to expand. | type = Mountain glacier | location = [[Mount Kilimanjaro]], [[Tanzania]] | coords = {{coord|03|04|50|S|37|20|42|E|type:glacier}} | area = | length = {{convert|.40|km|mi|abbr=on}} | thickness = | terminus = Talus | status = Retreating }} '''Balletto Glacier''' is near the summit of [[Mount Kilimanjaro]] in [[Tanzania]], on the southwest slope of the peak and is a small remnant of an [[Ice cap|icecap]] which once crowned the top of Mount Kilimanjaro.<ref name=young>{{cite web|last1=Young|first1=James A.T.|title=Glaciers of the Middle East and Africa - Glaciers of Africa|url=http://pubs.usgs.gov/pp/p1386g/africa.pdf|publisher=U. S. Geological Survey|accessdate=October 8, 2014|format=pdf|date=1991}}</ref> The glacier is situated at an elevation of between {{convert|5400|and|5000|m}}. Balletto Glacier is situated on the enormous {{convert|1200|m|adj=on}} rock wall known as the "Breach Wall" and is below Diamond Glacier. The two glaciers are connected by an enormous icicle which hangs down the rock face as much as {{convert|90|m|abbr=on}}.<ref>{{cite book|last1=Birkby|first1=Robert|title=Mountain Madness: Scott Fischer, Mount Everest & a Life Lived on High|date=February 1, 2009|publisher=Citadel|isbn=978-0806528762|pages=116–117|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-isMEDbYPccC&pg=PA116&lpg=PA116&dq=balletto+glacier&source=bl&ots=nxqgS2Vyyr&sig=3PoG2u6F4GQSZz4Xt3--41Ptv4I&hl=en&sa=X&ei=bKRfVOv-Laa4iQKf3IGYCQ&ved=0CB0Q6AEwADgK#v=onepage&q=balletto%20glacier&f=false|accessdate=October 9, 2014}}</ref>
