{{Infobox Venus crater | image = Barton crater.jpg | image_size = 200px | caption = ''[[Magellan (spacecraft)|Magellan]]'' radar image of Barton crater | coordinates = {{coord|27.4|N|337.5|E|globe:venus_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | diameter = 54 km | eponym = [[Clara Barton]] }}
'''Barton''' [[Impact crater|crater]] is a 54-km (32-mi) diameter crater on [[Venus]]. It is the size at which craters on Venus begin to possess [[Peak ring (crater)|peak-rings]] instead of a single central peak. The floor of Barton crater is flat and radar-dark, indicating possible infilling by lava flows sometime following the impact. Barton's central peak-ring is discontinuous and appears to have been disrupted or separated during or following the cratering process. The crater is named after [[Clara Barton]], the founder of the [[American Red Cross]].<ref>{{Cite web | title = Gazetteer of Planetary Nomenclature - Barton | publisher = [[International Astronomical Union]] | date = October 1, 2006 | url = http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/623?__fsk=-1618476416 | format = | doi = | accessdate = 2010-07-31}}</ref>
